{"article_id":"IwnE4USzWdbofEpJ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A `` breach of protocol '' at the hospital","depth":10},{"id":1,"text":"where Ebola victim Thomas Eric Duncan was treated","depth":11},{"id":2,"text":"before his death","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"led to the infection of a healthcare worker with the deadly virus ,","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"and other caregivers could potentially be exposed ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"federal health officials said Sunday.","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"The hospital worker , a woman","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"who was not identified by officials ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"wore protective gear","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"while treating the Liberian patient ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"and she has been unable to point to how the breach might have occurred ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"said Dr. Tom Frieden , head of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Duncan was the first person in the U.S.","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"diagnosed with Ebola .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"The CDC confirmed Sunday afternoon","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"that the woman had tested positive for Ebola - the first known case of the disease","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"being contracted or transmitted in the U.S .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"The missteps with the first patient and now the infection of a caregiver raised questions about assurances","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"given by U.S. health officials","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"that any American hospital should be able to treat an Ebola patient","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"and that the disease would be contained .","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"At a briefing in Atlanta , Frieden said","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"that at some point during Duncan 's treatment , `` there was a breach in protocol ,","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"and that breach in protocol resulted in this infection . ''","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"He added","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"that officials were `` deeply concerned '' by the infection of the worker .","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"President Barack Obama asked the CDC to move as quickly as possible","depth":5},{"id":27,"text":"in investigating the incident ,","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"the White House said .","depth":4},{"id":29,"text":"Dallas police stood guard outside her apartment complex","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"and told people not to go inside .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"Officers also knocked on doors ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"made automated phone calls","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"and passed out fliers","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"to notify people within a four-block radius about the situation ,","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"although Dallas authorities assured residents","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"the risk was confined to those","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"who have had close contact with the two Ebola patients .","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"The worker wore a gown , gloves , mask and shield","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"while she cared for Duncan during his second visit to Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital ,","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"said Dr. Daniel Varga of Texas Health Resources ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"which runs the hospital .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Duncan ,","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"who arrived in the U.S. from Liberia","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"to visit family Sept. 20 ,","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"first sought medical care for fever and abdominal pain Sept. 25 .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"He told a nurse","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"he had traveled from Africa ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"but he was sent home .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"He returned Sept. 28","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"and was placed in isolation","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"because of suspected Ebola .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"He died Wednesday .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Liberia is one of the three West African countries","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"most affected by the Ebola epidemic ,","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"which has killed more than 4,000 people ,","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"according to World Health Organization figures","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"published Friday .","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"The others are Sierra Leone and Guinea .","depth":4},{"id":59,"text":"Texas health officials have been closely monitoring nearly 50 people","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"who had or may have had close contact with Duncan in the days","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"after he started showing symptoms","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"but before he was diagnosed with the disease .","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"The healthcare worker reported a fever Friday night as part of a self-monitoring regimen","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"required by the CDC ,","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"Varga said .","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"Another person","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"who was described as a `` close contact '' of the health worker","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"has been proactively placed in isolation ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"he added ,","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"without elaborating on","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"where that person is being monitored .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"The hospital said","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"its emergency department is diverting ambulances to other hospitals ,","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"though still accepting walk-in patients .","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"Frieden said","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"officials are now evaluating","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"and will monitor any workers","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"who may have been exposed","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"while Duncan was in the hospital .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"Among the things","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"the CDC will investigate","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"is how the workers took off protective gear ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"because removing it incorrectly can lead to contamination .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Investigators will also look at dialysis and intubation","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"- the insertion of a breathing tube in a patient 's airway .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Both procedures have the potential","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"to spread the virus .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"`` We knew","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"a second case could be a reality ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"and we 've been preparing for this possibility , ''","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"said Dr. David Lakey , commissioner of the Texas Department of State Health Services .","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"`` We are broadening our team in Dallas","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"and working with extreme diligence","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"to prevent further spread . ''","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"Healthcare workers","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"treating Ebola patients","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"are among the most vulnerable ,","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"even if wearing protective gear .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"A Spanish nurse assistant recently became the first healthcare worker","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"infected outside West Africa during the ongoing outbreak .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"She helped care for two priests","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"who were brought to a Madrid hospital","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"and later died .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"More than 370 healthcare workers in West Africa have fallen ill or died","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"since the epidemic began earlier this year .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"In the health worker 's neighborhood , one police officer said","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"an industrial barrel outside contained hazardous waste","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"taken from inside the building .","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"Nearby residents periodically came out of their homes","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"to ask about the commotion .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"Kara Lutley ,","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"who lives a half-block from the complex ,","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"she never received a call or other emergency notice","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"and first heard about it on the news .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"`` I 'm not overly concerned","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"that I 'll get Ebola , ''","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"Officials said","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"they also received information","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"that there may be a pet in the healthcare worker 's apartment ,","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"and they have a plan in place","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"to care for the animal .","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"They do not believe","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"the pet has signs","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"of having contracted Ebola .","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"A dog","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"belonging to the Spanish nurse","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"was euthanized ,","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"drawing thousands of protests .","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"Ebola spreads through close contact with a symptomatic person 's bodily fluids , such as blood , sweat , vomit , feces , urine , saliva or semen .","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"Those fluids must have an entry point , like a cut or scrape","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"or someone touching the nose , mouth or eyes with contaminated hands ,","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"or being splashed .","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"The World Health Organization says","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"blood , feces and vomit are the most infectious fluids ,","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"while the virus is found in saliva","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"mostly","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"once patients are severely ill .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"The whole live virus has never been culled from sweat .","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"The trip was the culmination of decades of effort ,","depth":6},{"id":142,"text":"friends and family members said .","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"when Duncan arrived in Dallas ,","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"though he showed no symptoms ,","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"he had already been exposed to Ebola .","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"His neighbors in Liberia believe","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"Duncan become infected","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"when he helped a pregnant neighbor","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"who later died from it .","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"It was unclear if he knew about her diagnosis","depth":7},{"id":152,"text":"before traveling .","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"On Saturday , customs and health officials began taking the temperatures of passengers","depth":6},{"id":154,"text":"arriving at New York 's Kennedy International Airport from Liberia , Sierra Leone and Guinea in a stepped-up screening effort .","depth":6},{"id":155,"text":"The screenings will expand to four additional airports","depth":7},{"id":156,"text":"- New Jersey 's Newark Liberty , Washington Dulles , Chicago O'Hare and Hartsfield-Jackson in Atlanta -","depth":7},{"id":157,"text":"in the coming days .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":315,"left":210,"right":314,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":183,"right":209,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":183,"left":178,"right":182,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":174,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":169,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":163,"right":168,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":162,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162,"left":161,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":161,"left":160,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":160,"left":0,"right":159,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left"